law.text:
// EFFECTIVE UNTIL SEPTEMBER 30, 2013 PER CHAPTER 74 OF 2008 //
If authorized or directed by the United States Department of Labor, the Department may directly collect from employers the federal unemployment insurance tax set forth in the Federal Unemployment Tax Act, 26 U.S.C. § 3301 et seq.
The Department shall use funds derived from the collection of taxes collected under subsection (a) of this section only to administer programs and services designated under §§ 8-302 and 8-303 of this title.
